How to Play Shadow Fight 2?


Make sure you choose a weapon with blazing speed (for example, ornamental sabers, spinny knuckles, claws, kusarigama, or any other weapon you think is fast enough).


The second step is to decide what enhancements are most appropriate.


My suggestion would be to make enhancements that deal a lot of damage.


You should take a frenzy, bleeding, or time bomb. Bleeding and time bombs might not work well through his thick mechanical armor.


On the other hand, a frenzy can be activated with ease (depending on the power of the enchantment).


It is recommended that those who are not hotheaded like me use the life steal enchantment. This is an excellent enchantment for those who prefer to play defensively. With each successful hit, your health will be replenished for good (Titan also does the same).


It is an absolute fact that ranged weapons cannot be used against Titan.


If you are a defensive player, I suggest you take your position and use a time bomb or life steal to increase your chances of winning.


The defensive players have the best chance of winning. As for the offensive players, they should keep hurting the titan if they are going to win.


You don’t want to let him have a breathing area, but you also don’t want to get too close to him, or he will head-butt you or whip you like the Indian angry woman tries to clean cloth in anger with her head-butt.


Keep a safe distance from him as well, or he will bring you to him by means of his hydraulic mechanical arm or throw a freaking blue orb at you and whip you like you’re nothing to him. Don’t let him hit you, or else you are going to have a drastic decline in your health, and his health will also return.


I believe that the most powerful weapon you possess, which is your magic, needs to be used wisely, but before using them wisely, you’ll have to choose your magic wisely.


The most important enchantment of the game would be the torturer’s rage, the monk’s amulet, the lightning arrow or fire splash, the time bomb or bleeding enchantment, or the frenzy enchantment.


Oh, I completely forgot to mention the most important enchantment of the game.


The Tempest Rage can only be obtained by collecting all the Monk’s set gear.


Keep in mind that Titan is a slow but very intelligent monster. So be careful. He’s not someone who should be messed with.


I’ve faced Titan a few times, and he even made me achieve the achievement of losing 200 times.


